node.text:
Be unapologetically you, kid. 🤍

I wanted a board that says we welcome all books and their own life stories. The mint board will be where our book selfies and pictures of work they’re proud will go. I’m so ready to see it filled!

I’ll be adding these board letters along with the words “characters” and “genres” to my All Are Welcome Here Template resource. Link in profile to grab it now.

node.text:
Dry erase boards! 
The easiest space to create for their thoughts, to connect your grade level/class, and to bring that fun! My former teammates inspired this space, and I love how they include a “finish that drawing” and “idioms of the week”. My boards include a read aloud hashtag reflection, podcast reflection, class shoutouts, and a finish that sentence board.

node.text: Idk what it is, but I love awkward wall spaces! Challenge accepted on this wall space! I added some book cover faves here completely inspired by @teachergolz, and I couldn’t love it more. I’ll change them out as students share their recommendations this year. 🤩

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ashley Ramirez on August 08, 2021. May be an illustration of 3 people and book.

node.text:
All characters with different life experiences, who we recognize ourselves in and don’t, and found throughout different genres welcome here! I went for a poster size with this print and it went up in a book nook area last year.✨

I definitely felt like this resource needed to be expanded to include mathematicians, scientists, artists, creators, cultures, writers, and more. I included templates for you to insert your own images. Add student pics, add examples of famous people, mix up both! I wish I could include the character images themselves for the book themed templates, but I walk you through how to do it. So easy!

Want to make this a bulletin board? I do!!! Stay tuned for the board kit coming tomorrow! If you already own this you’ll be able to download again for the update.💛

*Please note that I sell the template and guide on how to do this with your own characters. I do not sell the templates with characters on them. Just so we’re clear. 😆

node.text:
COLLABORATORS/FRIENDS✨
Partner Cards = the least amount of prep ever and the greatest organizational tool for the entire year. I’m working on printing mine now. Grab these editable partner cards using the link in profile. Read on for more details!

▶️HOW DOES IT WORK?
During the first week of school/new nine weeks/whenever you want students establish each partner by writing their names down on each line. I’ve made myself a partner before too! I let them choose and have had great success with challenging them to branch out, but you can preselect partners too.

▶️WHERE DO THEY GO?
Laminate and velcro to desks, tape to agendas, or you can even put them on their notebooks. I plan on taping to their notebooks, since we’re departmentalized. 😉

▶️WHAT IF A STUDENT MOVES OR YOU HAVE AN ODD NUMBER?
I readjust by having that student take the place of the one that moved, I’ll add myself to their list, or I make a group of 3 if needed.

▶️WHY CREATE A PARTNER SYSTEM?
I’ve partnered on the fly, and it’s simply extra work on my end to make sure the pairs are just right. That’s extra time taken away from the activity. This also makes it easier if you have a sub. It takes away some of that anxiety of not knowing who they’re going to work with, and it fosters a relationship with five different classmates. Lastly, you’re going to have fun saying the names out loud! Trust me! 😆

node.text:
This cart never got used last year! I was so excited to finally have created an all in one space for student work and multiple classes. It also needed to be vertical in order to fit anywhere. 

This cart is coming with me into this new year along with some changes! Yup, giving pen pals another go. I’ve had a mixed experience with it, and this time I’m partnering with a close friend. Snail mail is making a comeback and I’m here for it! 👏🏼🙌🏼

node.text:
I always love to personalize our space with class pics of all our memories! They’ll keep returning to look too and get excited for anything new on there. Guaranteed. 🤍 At the end of the year those pics turn into end of year keepsakes for all of them!

Grab my Better Together bulletin board kit that comes with editable square photo holders. I add hashtags for moments I want to capture and for traditions specific to us. ✨

Swipe to see the new board letters I’m adding tonight! Link in profile.

node.text:
Feels so good stocking up on all the essentials I use throughout the year! I always shop my local @heb for BTS, and this year they’re offering 15% off for educators. I just signed myself up at heb.com/teachers using my school email. You can find the link in my stories to grab your coupon too!
#hebteacher #ad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ashley Ramirez on July 25, 2021. May be an image of text.

node.text:
EDITABLE EARLY FINISHER TASKS
I took my early finisher tasks and went digital with them last year! 

Want to create a graphic novel, question what happens to slime in space, draw while listening to Yo-Yo Ma playing the cello, find the answers to all of your wonderings or submit them, and research a topic of your choice? I’m here for you, kid! 💛 

There’s 40 premade/editable digital tasks hyperlinked and ready to go for you in Google Slides. I kept in mind that I cannot update all the things, so these tasks reflect ongoing activities students can do independently. I walk you through each one in the guide included and explain how to share in Google Classroom.

They’ve been added to my editable print version, which means options! 🔗Link in profile. 

If you want just digital, then I’ve shared in my stories highlight called “new”. 😊
